launchd E2E — install → kill → re-start round-trip
====================================================

# Clean slate
$ bash scripts/launchd/uninstall.sh
(nothing to uninstall — /Users/liuzhixiong/Library/LaunchAgents/com.cursorpointer.plist not present)
$ pkill cursor-pointer; sleep 1; curl /health
(API down — expected)

# Install + manual start
$ bash scripts/launchd/install.sh
✓ installed → /Users/liuzhixiong/Library/LaunchAgents/com.cursorpointer.plist
✓ active in launchctl
$ launchctl start com.cursorpointer; sleep 4; curl /health
{"ok":true,"name":"cursor-pointer","version":"0.1.0"}

# Kill .app and re-launch via launchctl
$ pkill cursor-pointer; sleep 2; curl /health
(API down — expected after kill)
$ launchctl start com.cursorpointer; sleep 4; curl /health
{"ok":true,"name":"cursor-pointer","version":"0.1.0"}

# Final state — LaunchAgent stays registered
$ launchctl list | grep com.cursorpointer
35284	0	application.com.cursorpointer.app.99343326.99343329
-	0	com.cursorpointer

Conclusion: install.sh registers the agent, launchctl can start/restart the
app, uninstall.sh is idempotent, and at next login the .app will auto-launch.
